title: Veeam License
agents: veeam_rest
catalog: app/veeam
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the Veeam Backup & Replication license status via the REST API.

 It reports:
 - License status (Valid, Invalid, Expired)
 - License expiration date and days remaining
 - Support contract expiration
 - Instance license usage and utilization percentage
 - Socket and capacity license usage (if applicable)

 The check returns:
 - OK: License is valid and not expiring soon
 - WARN: License or support contract expiring within threshold (default: 30 days)
 - WARN: Instance usage exceeds warning threshold (default: 80%)
 - CRIT: License invalid or expired
 - CRIT: License expiring within critical threshold (default: 7 days)
 - CRIT: Instance usage exceeds critical threshold (default: 95%)

 Configurable thresholds for license expiration, support expiration,
 and instance usage levels.

discovery:
 One service is created for the Veeam license.
